<TITLE> College teacher killed, 4 hit in Kushtia drive-by shooting </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Kushtia, Aug 15 (bdnews24.com)  Unknown gunmen, in a drive-by shooting, killed a college teacher and injured four others, including a local Awami League leader, at Bheramata Upazila in Kushtia on Saturday, police said. Banda Fattah Mohon, a teacher at Bheramara BJM College, died after being admitted to Kushtia General Hospital, said Kushtia superintendent of police Shahabuddin Khan. Khan said six armed assailants rode by on two motorcycles and opened fire at the vcitims who were sitting in an open fronted clothes store at around 9pm. Of the injured, one was Meherul Alam, 56, joint general secretary of Bheramara Upazila's Awami League unit. The others were contractors Enamul Haq, 50, and Anwarul Haq, 48, and a Krishi Bank official, Hafizur Rahman, 48. The injured were being treated at Bheramara Upazila Health Complex and Kushtia General Hospital, said Khan. He said police were deployed at key points in the town to hunt down the shooters. bdn
